title: UofTCTF 2026
description:
UofTCTF 2026 is the annual capture-the-flag competition organized by the UofTCTF team. This year’s event will take place online from January 9, 2026, at 7:00 PM EST to January 11, 2026, at 7:00 PM EST. It will be a jeopardy-style CTF with classic categories like web, pwn, crypto, rev, forensics, and misc.

Join the event discord server: https://discord.gg/4mQP8Tk3JE

Thank you to our generous sponsors, without whom we could not run this event:
- Dataflow Security
- Zellic
- Offsec
- Binary Ninja
- BugCrowd
- KPMG Canada
- UofT ITS
- UofT DCS

Infra sponsored by goo.gle/ctfsponsorship

title: SWIMMER OSINT CTF
description:
Story Driven CTF for Beginners (online JP Domestic)
SWIMMER OSINT CTF
by DIVER OSINT CTF

Jan. 17th 2026 (Sat)
AM 3:10 START (UTC)
Competition Time: 12 hours (END at PM 3:10 UTC)
Team Members: 1 - 6 people
Language: Japanese / English

NOTE
Unlike the DIVER OSINT CTF, the SWIMMER OSINT CTF is primarily a domestic event. 
Most challenge materials will be in Japanese, so you may encounter some language barriers.
That being said, participants from anywhere in the world are welcome, and we will provide support in both English and Japanese.

For more information, follow the official DIVER OSINT CTF account on X
X: @DIVER_OSINT_CTF

title: Jeanne d'Hack CTF 2026 | 3ème Édition
description: Jeanne d'Hack CTF est une compétition de Capture The Flag qui mettra au défi vos compétences en sécurité informatique. Avec des épreuves variées, du Web à la cryptographie, c'est une occasion parfaite pour tester vos connaissances et collaborer avec d'autres passionnés. Rejoignez-nous pour une journée de défis stimulants et d'apprentissage !
